      "content": "The \"living Constitution\" view is practically necessary because society and technology evolve far faster than legislative bodies can amend the foundational document. Relying only on the literal text would leave citizens vulnerable to outdated laws that fail to protect modern liberties, like digital privacy. Therefore, interpreting the Constitution as a dynamic guide, rather than a rigid statute, allows it to remain a relevant shield for civil rights across changing times.",
      "source": "target",
